quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  25,21,"And those who do not expect to meet Us said: why was not the angels sent down to us, or why do we not see our Master? They have certainly been arrogant about themselves, and they rebelled, a great rebellion"
  25,22,"A day that they see the angels, there is no good news for the guilty ones on that day, and they (the angles) say: a forbidden ban (that you receive God's mercy)"
  25,23,And We turn to the work they did and We make it scattered dust
  25,24,"On that day, inhabitants of the garden have a good living place and better relaxing place"
  25,25,A day that the sky with the clouds splits apart and the angels are sent down in a great descent
  25,26,"on that day the true rule belongs to the beneficent, and it is a difficult day for the disbelievers"
  25,27,"And a day that the wrongdoer bites his hands, saying: I wish I had taken the way along with the messenger"
  25,28,"Woe to me, I wish I had not taken so and so as a friend"
  25,29,"He has certainly led me away from the reminder after it came to me, and Satan is a deserter of the human being (as he declares himself clear of the human being)"
  25,30,"And the messenger says: my Master, indeed my people made this Quran abandoned"
  25,31,And that is how We made an enemy from the guilty ones for every messenger . And your Master is enough as a guide and a helper
  25,32,"And those who disbelieved said: why was not the Quran sent down to him all at once? It is like that, so that We strengthen your heart with it, and We recited it to you distinctly (and slowly)"
  25,33,And they do not give you an example (or question) unless We bring you the truth and the best explanation (of it)
  25,34,"Those who are gathered (lying down) on their faces into hell, they are in worst position and are far (lost) from the way"
  25,35,And We have certainly given Moses the book and appointed his brother Aaron with him as his minister
  25,36,"Then We said: you both go to the people who denied Our signs. Then We destroyed them, a total destruction"
  25,37,"And We drowned people of Noah when they denied the messengers and We made them a sign for the people, and We prepared a painful punishment for the wrongdoers"
  25,38,And (We also destroyed) Aad and Thamud and the inhabitants of the Rass (the well) and many generations between them
  25,39,"And to each one We gave examples, and We destroyed them all, a total destruction"
  25,40,"And they have certainly come upon the town that was rained on, the bad rain. Did they not used to see it? No, but they do not expect resurrection"
  25,41,"And when they see you, they only take you as a joke (saying): is this the one whom God sent as a messenger"
  25,42,"He almost led us away from our gods, if we had not persevered on them. They will know who is more off the (right) way when they see the punishment"
  25,43,Did you see he who took his desire as his god? Are you his advocate
  25,44,"Or do you think that most of them listen or understand? They are like animals. No, but they are more lost from a (right) way"
  25,45,"Did you not see how you Master makes the shadow longer, and if He wanted He would have made it stand still, and We made the sun its guide"
  25,46,"Then We pull it toward Ourselves, an easy pull"
  25,47,"And He is the One who made the night as a cover for you, and the sleep as a rest, and He made the day to rise up (and work)"
  25,48,"And He is the One who sent the winds as good news before His mercy, and We sent down pure water from the sky"
  25,49,"In order to bring the dead land back to life with it, and make Our numerous creation of livestock and human beings drink it"
  25,50,"And We have certainly explained it to them (in various ways) so that they may take notice, but most people refuse to be anything except ungrateful (and disbeliever)"
  25,51,"And if We wanted, We would have raised a warner in every town"
  25,52,"So do not obey the disbelievers, and try hard against them with it (Quran), a great try"